\pard\sa220\sl280\slmult1\b\fs28 1. System Overview\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 `dgu.ac` is not just a brochure site. Based on the public website structure, it functions as a university discovery, admissions, and student-services platform with three distinct surfaces:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Public university website at `www.dgu.ac`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Admissions application flow at `admissions.dgu.ac`\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Student operations handed off to `student.camu.in`\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 From the public site, DGU currently exposes:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Schools and a large program catalog\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Admission process pages, fee structures, scholarships, hostel and transport information, and refund policy\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab News Center with categories such as Campus News, Admission News, Placement News, and Events News\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Faculty directory and leadership pages\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Downloads and brochures\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab External integrations such as a virtual tour hosted on object storage and a separate student portal\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 Architectural conclusion:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab DGU already behaves like a split-domain platform: `www` for discovery, `admissions` for applicant conversion, and an external student portal for post-admission operations.\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab The right backend target is a modular platform with clear bounded contexts: Public CMS, Admissions, Identity, Media, Notifications, and Student-system Integration.\par
\par
