\pard\sa220\sl280\slmult1\b\fs28 4. Frontend to Backend Interaction\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sl276\slmult1\b\fs24 4.1 API Style\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 Recommendation: REST-first architecture with optional GraphQL later for internal dashboard aggregation.\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 Why:\par
\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Public content and program pages are highly cacheable and map well to REST\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab Admissions workflows are stateful and easier to govern via REST resources\par
\pard\li360\fi-180\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22\bullet\tab GraphQL is not necessary at initial scale and adds operational complexity\par
\par
\pard\sa180\sl276\slmult1\b\fs24 4.2 Data Flow\b0\fs22\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 Client -> CDN -> Next.js frontend -> API Gateway or BFF -> NestJS backend -> Redis cache -> PostgreSQL\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 For async operations:\par
\par
\pard\sa120\sl240\slmult1\f0\fs22 Backend -> Queue -> Notification workers / ERP sync / media processing\par
\par
